[[File:Festival International de Percussions de Longueuil.JPG|thumb|The [[Tam-Tams]] at the International Percussion Festival.]]
The '''International Percussion Festival''' ({{lang-fr|Festival international de percussions}}) is an annual [[festival]] of [[percussion instrument]]s in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]]. The festival takes place on different places around Montreal each July over a period of six days . The festival is a [[nonprofit organization]] presenting over 500 local and international musicians, on 4 stages, attracting close to 200,000 spectators annually.<ref name="loto">{{cite web|url=http://lotoquebec.com/rendezvous/nav/en/festivals-events/international-percussion-festival-of-longueuil|title=International Percussion Festival of Longueuil PrintPrint|year=2012|work=Les Rendez-Vous Loto-Québec|publisher=[[Loto-Québec]]|accessdate=28 June 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508174457/http://lotoquebec.com/rendezvous/nav/en/festivals-events/international-percussion-festival-of-longueuil|archivedate=8 May 2014|df=}}</ref> The Percussion Festival whas a different theme each year.

The festival was founded in 2002 by Gilbert Lucu and France Cadieux. The first festival was held in [[Venise-en-Québec, Quebec|Venise-en-Québec]] near the [[United States]] border, although was moved to [[Longueuil]] starting in its second year. In 2015, the festival was at the [[Old Port of Montreal]]. In 2016, it will be in [[Verdun, Quebec|Verdun]].

