{{Infobox song contest |name = Melodifestivalen |year = 1975 |final = 15 February 1975 |presenters = [[Karin Falck]] |venue = [[Sveriges Radio|SR]] Television Centre, [[Gothenburg]] |vote = Regional juries |winner = "[[Jennie, Jennie]]" by [[Lasse Berghagen]] }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1975''' was the selection for the 16th song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 15th time that this system of picking a song had been used. 10 songwriters were selected by [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT1|TV1]] but was not broadcast on radio.
