{{Infobox Film Festival | name = Portland Film Festival | image = | caption = | number = | founded = 2013 | location = [[Portland, Oregon]] | language = | date = August 27 through September 1, 2013 | website = [http://www.portlandfilmfestival.com www.portlandfilmfestival.com] }}
'''Portland Film Festival''' is a non-profit independent film festival that is held in several local theaters in [[Portland, Oregon]]. It was founded in 2013 by Joshua Leake and Jay Cornelius. The first film festival was held from August 27 through September 1, 2013 and featured networking events, workshops, a [[beer garden]], and food carts.<ref>{{cite web|title='For The Love Of Film': Portland's Newest Cinema Festival Debuts|url=http://www.opb.org/artsandlife/article/for-love-of-film-portlands-newest-cinema-festival-debuts/|publisher=OPB|accessdate=9 December 2013}}</ref> 83 films were shown in the inaugural festival and over 600 were submitted for consideration at the festival.<ref>{{cite web|title=Festival Spotlight Friday: Portland Film Festival is the Artist Colony of Your Dreams|url=http://www.moviemaker.com/festivals/festival-spotlight-friday-portland-film-festival-is-the-artist-colony-of-your-dreams/|publisher=MovieMaker|accessdate=9 December 2013}}</ref> Highlights of the event included [[Andy Mingo]]'s short film ''Romance'', which was based on a [[Chuck Palahniuk]] short story.<ref>{{cite web|title=Palahniuk helps readers (and now filmgoers) find 'Romance'|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/movies/index.ssf/2013/08/palahniuk_helps_readers_and_no.html|publisher=Oregon Live|accessdate=9 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dispatches from the Portland Film Festival: Chuck Palahniuk Hands Out Stuffed Kittens|url=http://www.wweek.com/portland/blog-30618-dispatches_from_the_portland_film_festival_chuck_p.html|publisher=WWeek|accessdate=9 December 2013}}</ref>
